        "content": "<p>I have a finite collection of nonzero elements <code>f : ι → R</code> and a prime, or at least non-1, ideal <code>p</code>. Do we have a way to find <code>f' : ι → R</code> such that not all <code>f' i</code> are in <code>p</code>, and <code>a * f' i = b * f i</code> for some <code>a, b</code>? Do we have this where <code>f</code> actually goes to the field of fractions of <code>R</code>?</p>\n<p>I remember we had something along these lines. Perhaps I'm thinking <a href=\"https://leanprover-community.github.io/mathlib_docs/find/fractional_ideal.exists_not_mem_one_of_ne_bot\">docs#fractional_ideal.exists_not_mem_one_of_ne_bot</a> does more than it actually did...</p>",
